'''Slaver guilds''' were organizations set up and geared towards the legal or illegal acquisition of [[Slavery/Legends|slaves]], mainly from worlds in the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]]. They enjoyed an increase in trade following the rise of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and the legalization of the trade, previously illegal under the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]].<ref name="UGSV">{{InsiderCite|89|Underworld: A Galaxy of Scum and Villainy}}</ref>

[[Terrinald Screed/Legends|Terrinald Screed]] noted that of the various organizations who dealt in the slave trade, only three were worth mentioning: the [[Zygerrian Slavers Guild]], the [[Thalassian slavers/Legends|Thalassian Pirates]], and the relatively new [[Karazak Slavers' Cooperative/Legends|Karazak Slavers Cooperative]].<ref name="UGSV" />

When the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] rose to power, they outlawed slavery, although it continued to operate within criminal havens. By this time, slaver guilds such as the [[Thalassian slavers/Legends|Thalassian slavers]] and [[Zygerrian Slavers Guild]] were considered to be remnants of their former selves, but continued to provide a steady stream of slaves to the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] [[Kajidic/Legends|Kajidics]] and other similar organizations.<ref name="EGWT">''[[The Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology]]''</ref>

